n of cataracts.  The glasses should be worn any time patients are exposed to direct or indirect sunlight, whether they are outdoors or exposed through a window.  Because erythema and/or burning due to photochemotherapy and sunburn due to sun exposure are additive, patients should not sunbathe for 48 hours after photochemotherapy.', 'Synergism', 'Caution is advised and pharmacologic response to methoxsalen therapy should be carefully monitored if concomitant use of other photosensitizing agents cannot be avoided.', 'Moderate', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/286522/', '', 'Acitretin, Etretinate, Trioxsalen, Tazarotene, Calcipotriol, Trioxsalen, Calcitriol', 'Methoxsalen, Tazarotene, Methoxsalen, Calcipotriol, Calcitriol', 1767369485);
